      "writtenOn": "2017-07-06T14:37:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think that\u0027s okay. The signature of onGenerateTexture can change at this point - no clients have their own generators that override that virtual. (It\u0027s not even possible anymore, because GrTextureProxy.h is in src, not include).\n\nI\u0027d suggest using the SkTransferFunctionBehavior enum, because that is really the thing that differentiates color space xform canvas from colorspace-on-surface behavior). Similarly, when making the newly tagged lazy image (in onMakeColorSpace), you could retain the passed-in behavior enum along with the color space, so that we could respect both kinds of requests via that API.",
      "parentUuid": "df24a386_7ce7b624",
      "revId": "fa6d5121fbc81f12552c292e8ca045d675a82e21",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
